						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged. It seems to state that the temple authorities received only 10 <hi rend="italic">kāsu</hi> out of 50 promised by Śōḻakōṉāṟ for the improvement of a temple land (?) called <hi rend="italic">Irumuḍis11ōḻa-perumas11akkal</hi> for the maintenance of a lamp, and this amount was found insufficient for the purpose. Further details are lost. <hi rend="bold">Irumuḍi-Chōḷa</hi> was a probably surname of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> It was also a title conferred by Rājēndradēva on his uncle Gaṅgaikoṇḍa (<hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> Vol. III, No 58.)</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
